\b\par
Changes to Extended BASIC compiler v2.1\b0\par
The most important changes are the repair of several bugs. The line number bug caused certain line numbers (235,238,239,240,254) to compile incorrectly. The sprite bug crashed the computer when you deleted a sprite  that was not in motion. A bug in the print routine kept lines from scrolling properly. These have all been fixed in version 2.1\par
The following was added to the compiler:\par
CALL PEEK\par
CALL LOAD\par
MAX\par
MIN\par
RPT$\par
The manual has been updated and expanded.\par
